title: 01 Find where a macro is defined

!! Scenario

You're looking at one of your tiddlers and it contains a macro call like `<<some-macro>>`. The macro produces some output, but you don't know which tiddler defines it.

!! Try this prompt

> ''"In the tiddler `MyTiddler` I have the call `<<some-macro>>`. Where is `some-macro` defined and on which line?"''

Tip: replace `MyTiddler` and `some-macro` with the real names from your wiki.

!! Response you'll see

The AI will reply something like:

<<<
The `some-macro` procedure is defined in the tiddler ''Tools/Buttons'' on line 4. It's automatically available everywhere because `Tools/Buttons` is tagged `$:/tags/Global`. Inside `MyTiddler`, the `<<some-macro>>` call expands to a button widget produced by that procedure.
<<<

!! Behind the scenes

The AI calls `inspect_pos` with the wikitext containing the macro call and your tiddler title as `context`. The tool annotates each rendered node with attributes that trace it back to its source:

* `v="some-macro"`: names the procedure that produced the node
* `p="1:4"`: line 4 of the tiddler at index `1` in the title-map
* the title-map header `[0=MyTiddler 1=Tools/Buttons]` maps the index to the tiddler name

For the full attribute reference, see [[Inspect Tools]].
